articles.author: Michael Lee
articles.title: Australian snorkeler survives crocodile attack by prying jaws off his head: 'Wrong place, at the wrong time' - Fox News
articles.description: An Australian man snorkeling in coastal water was able to survive multiple attacks by a large crocodile, using his hands to pry its mouth open to release its grip.
articles.content:
An Australian man was able to escape multiple attacks from a saltwater crocodile, including having to pry the animal's jaws open to get his head out of its grip.
